        "creation_date": 1359765803,
        "body": "<p>What it means is probably that, if a class has no other methods or fields, then you only access it for the singleton, so the singleton is only created when demanded. Otherwise, for example<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>class Foo \n{\n    public static final Foo foo = new Foo();\n\n    public static int x() { return 0; }\n}\n\nclass AnotherClass\n{\n    void test() \n    {\n        print(Foo.x());\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>here, <code>foo<\/code> was instantiated, though it was never asked for.<\/p>\n\n<p>But it's ok to have private static methods/fields, so others won't trigger class initialization by accident.<\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 14657403,
